WEBVTT

00:02.536 --> 00:04.838
[ School bell rings ]

00:04.872 --> 00:09.977
**

00:10.010 --> 00:11.011
[ Knock on door ]

00:11.045 --> 00:14.382
**

00:14.415 --> 00:15.883
[ Gasps ]

00:15.916 --> 00:19.687
Oh. My. Giraffe.

00:19.720 --> 00:20.654
[ Air whooshes ]

00:20.688 --> 00:21.722
[ School bell rings ]

00:21.755 --> 00:23.091
Standardized test scores,
coming through!

00:23.124 --> 00:24.192
Out of the way!

00:24.225 --> 00:25.393
[ Motor whirs ]

00:25.426 --> 00:27.828
Now, that's almost too sharp.

00:27.861 --> 00:29.097
**

00:29.130 --> 00:30.698
The test results are in.

00:30.731 --> 00:32.700
Dylan DiMeo...

00:32.733 --> 00:34.868
is the smartest kid
in the grade.

00:34.902 --> 00:36.170
[ Pencil clatters ]

00:36.204 --> 00:37.605
I'm Dylan Danger,

00:37.638 --> 00:40.608
and this is
Too-Long-Cord-Bungee.

00:41.709 --> 00:42.610
Whee!

00:42.643 --> 00:43.944
[ Thumps ]

00:43.977 --> 00:45.546
Are we sure there hasn't been
some sort of mistake?

00:45.579 --> 00:46.714
We ran it twice.

00:46.747 --> 00:50.451
That bush is the smartest kid
in the district.

00:50.484 --> 00:53.087
Dylan, you're...smart!

00:53.121 --> 00:54.088
I know!

00:54.122 --> 00:55.623
I had my finger
over the lens.

00:55.656 --> 00:56.857
Can we do it again?
Yeah.

00:56.890 --> 00:57.858
-No!
-No!
-No!

00:57.891 --> 01:01.962
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:01.995 --> 01:03.531
**

01:03.564 --> 01:06.400
Mikey always wanted
to be like his big brother.

01:06.434 --> 01:08.902
He wanted his hair
like Ben's,

01:08.936 --> 01:10.971
wanted to dance like Ben.

01:11.004 --> 01:12.240
**

01:12.273 --> 01:13.274
Now?

01:13.307 --> 01:14.742
[ Clicking ]

01:14.775 --> 01:16.777
Ben wants jeans
like mine.

01:16.810 --> 01:17.778
**

01:17.811 --> 01:19.113
[ Maya sniffles ]

01:19.147 --> 01:21.449
Okay, be honest --

01:21.482 --> 01:24.318
if you were
the 2019 Abilities Expo,

01:24.352 --> 01:27.221
and our company were at you,
showing that,

01:27.255 --> 01:29.623
wouldn't we be
the toast of you?

01:29.657 --> 01:31.792
[ Voice breaking ]
That video is as good

01:31.825 --> 01:34.328
as that question was
hard to follow.

01:34.362 --> 01:36.997
I had one thought.
The slogan?

01:37.030 --> 01:38.132
"Two special-needs moms

01:38.166 --> 01:40.768
making a difference
in the lives of families

01:40.801 --> 01:42.903
with children
with disabilities"?

01:42.936 --> 01:44.838
It doesn't exactly
roll off the tongue.

01:46.340 --> 01:48.276
-Kenneth, real quick...
-Huh?

01:48.309 --> 01:50.311
[ Lowered voice ] Look, I know
you haven't been with Melanie

01:50.344 --> 01:51.645
for very long,

01:51.679 --> 01:55.316
but as someone who is married
to a woman like her...

01:55.349 --> 01:57.451
nobody wants
your suggestions.

01:57.485 --> 02:00.421
I think they should give away
keychains at the convention.

02:00.454 --> 02:02.122
Beautiful idea...
Yeah.

02:02.156 --> 02:03.791
I'm gonna strangle it
in its crib.

02:03.824 --> 02:05.326
Because we don't matter.

02:05.359 --> 02:07.795
Melanie: This convention is
gonna be our coming-out party.

02:07.828 --> 02:11.932
Vogue. Vanity Fair.
SoCal Abilities Journal.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.367
I mean,
except for the first two,

02:13.401 --> 02:14.435
they're all
gonna be there.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.503
Mm.

02:15.536 --> 02:18.372
"You're going to
a convention? When?"

02:18.406 --> 02:20.208
Well, we'll be gone
tomorrow and then Saturday.

02:21.675 --> 02:22.643
Rude.

02:22.676 --> 02:25.379
**

02:25.413 --> 02:26.947
"Pack your bags.

02:26.980 --> 02:30.551
I was invited to
an overnight college visit

02:30.584 --> 02:34.021
but skipped because
Mom would want to go.

02:34.054 --> 02:38.158
But she has a" -- C-O--
"convention this weekend."

02:39.760 --> 02:41.695
So you want me to come?

02:41.729 --> 02:43.030
Well, totally.

02:43.063 --> 02:45.533
We can have some bro time,
maybe meet some ladies.

02:45.566 --> 02:46.967
"I've got Izzy,

02:47.000 --> 02:50.571
but you can get rejected
by some college girls."

02:50.604 --> 02:52.573
I know!
Dylan thought making

02:52.606 --> 02:54.007
that "Rejection Bingo" game
was a burn,

02:54.041 --> 02:57.044
but I'm a college girl
and an over 6'2" girl away

02:57.077 --> 02:59.680
from winning that
Chinese finger trap.

02:59.713 --> 03:02.149
I can't believe you're
gonna do a college tour

03:02.182 --> 03:03.484
without your mummy.

03:03.517 --> 03:04.518
It'll be great.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.520
The train will drop us off
right there.

03:06.554 --> 03:08.722
JJ's set up in this awesome
accessible dorm...

03:08.756 --> 03:11.259
But what if you get a little
something on your face?

03:11.292 --> 03:13.527
Or if a girl wants to see
a picture of you

03:13.561 --> 03:15.329
when you were a baby
in the tub?

03:15.363 --> 03:16.430
[ Door opens ]

03:16.464 --> 03:17.431
Load 'em up!

03:17.465 --> 03:18.599
All right, my loves.

03:18.632 --> 03:19.867
Off you go.
Have fun at college.

03:19.900 --> 03:21.669
Who's ready for two moms
to change the lives

03:21.702 --> 03:23.704
of children in families
of kids with disabilities?

03:23.737 --> 03:26.374
I'm ready for two moms to make
a difference in families

03:26.407 --> 03:28.609
of children who live
with disabilities.

03:28.642 --> 03:29.710
[ Lowered voice ]
They both got it wrong.

03:29.743 --> 03:30.744
It's so bad.

03:30.778 --> 03:31.745
What's that?

03:31.779 --> 03:34.181
Mnh. Nothing. Kenneth?

03:34.214 --> 03:36.016
I -- I'm carrying a box!

03:36.049 --> 03:37.851
**

03:37.885 --> 03:40.020
You want to see me
about brain stuff?

03:40.053 --> 03:42.122
Dylan, my most
promising student.

03:42.155 --> 03:43.724
I ain't promised
nothin' to no one

03:43.757 --> 03:45.626
what don't promise me
somethin' first.

03:45.659 --> 03:47.628
Okay, I'm gonna get
right to the point --

03:47.661 --> 03:49.263
I became a teacher
to change lives,

03:49.297 --> 03:50.464
so when I saw the gap

03:50.498 --> 03:52.466
between your test scores
and your grades,

03:52.500 --> 03:55.769
I knew I had a student who was
primed for a breakthrough.

03:55.803 --> 03:58.038
So...
[ Sighs ]

03:58.071 --> 03:59.773
Why you no smart
for school stuff?

03:59.807 --> 04:01.074
I don't know.

04:01.108 --> 04:03.377
Whenever I try to read
or listen to a teacher,

04:03.411 --> 04:04.912
I just get so annoyed.

04:04.945 --> 04:07.047
They just become this
know-it-all that won't shut up.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.248
That's fascinating.

04:08.282 --> 04:10.284
And it's only when they try
to teach you things?

04:10.318 --> 04:12.786
Like, if I talked about
a big old plate of nachos...

04:12.820 --> 04:15.155
Heck, yeah.
Where those nachos at?

04:15.188 --> 04:16.957
But if I say that they are
native to Mexico,

04:16.990 --> 04:18.058
population 130 million --

04:18.091 --> 04:19.827
No, make it stop!
I can't handle it.

04:19.860 --> 04:21.329
Aha! Don't run from it.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.731
Who am I?!

04:23.764 --> 04:26.567
No. You!

04:26.600 --> 04:28.469
Mr. Powers' voice:
I'm Ray, aren't I?

04:28.502 --> 04:29.803
It's time!

04:29.837 --> 04:31.739
For so many years,
we've been focused on our kids,

04:31.772 --> 04:33.341
and now we can use
all the lessons we've learned

04:33.374 --> 04:34.942
to help a world
of JJs and Logans.

04:34.975 --> 04:36.510
Every battle
is about to pay off.

04:36.544 --> 04:38.446
Every indignity,
every fight...

04:38.479 --> 04:39.447
[ Strained ]
Every hernia...

04:39.480 --> 04:40.848
It was all
for this moment.

04:40.881 --> 04:43.517
[ Triumphant music plays ]
[ Sighs ]

04:43.551 --> 04:46.086
These are our people.

04:46.119 --> 04:47.020
**

04:47.054 --> 04:49.156
Uh-oh.
Except for her.

04:49.189 --> 04:50.958
I had a doozie with that
physical therapist.

04:50.991 --> 04:53.126
Oh, well, if we're avoiding
people we've made enemies with,

04:53.160 --> 04:54.462
we probably
shouldn't go that way.

04:54.495 --> 04:56.296
Or that way.
School I egged.

04:56.330 --> 04:58.699
Ooh. Insurance lady
I "Groundhog Day-ed."

04:58.732 --> 05:00.601
[ Chuckles ]
That was involved.

05:00.634 --> 05:02.470
Fought with her,
fought with her...

05:02.503 --> 05:04.672
Oh, she's cool --
although I fought with her.

05:04.705 --> 05:06.139
Mnh.
[ Breathes sharply ]

05:06.173 --> 05:07.841
It seems that "our people"

05:07.875 --> 05:10.878
consist pretty solidly
of folks that hate us.

05:10.911 --> 05:12.446
P-Plan B.
L-Let's focus on the big fish.

05:12.480 --> 05:13.514
Okay, we'll wow
the magazine people,

05:13.547 --> 05:14.615
and then
we'll sneak out of here

05:14.648 --> 05:15.783
before all these people
kill us.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.385
You guys put
your heads down.

05:17.418 --> 05:19.353
I'll block you
with this sign.

05:19.387 --> 05:22.456
**

05:22.490 --> 05:24.992
Ah. They still seem
to know it's you.

05:25.025 --> 05:26.059
[ Lowered voice ]
Y-You do realize

05:26.093 --> 05:27.528
that they're
on the front?

05:27.561 --> 05:29.162
[ Lowered voice ] Yeah, yeah.
I-I know. I think it's funny.

05:29.196 --> 05:31.465
Dude, college is crazy.

05:31.499 --> 05:32.866
You know
the co-ed bathroom?

05:32.900 --> 05:36.003
I just went next to a lady
who's taking a shower.

05:36.036 --> 05:37.304
Oh. Who's your friend?

05:37.337 --> 05:39.407
I'm Alan, and there are
no co-ed bathrooms here.

05:40.240 --> 05:42.376
Okay!
Let's get this tour started.

05:42.410 --> 05:46.313
No need. It's like playing
the claw machine.

05:46.346 --> 05:49.049
[ Mechanical whir ]

05:50.350 --> 05:52.119
Hey! I got a "me"!

05:54.254 --> 05:56.424
"I'm excited
for college life.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.258
Start making
my own decisions."

05:58.291 --> 05:59.693
Big decision tonight --

05:59.727 --> 06:01.595
dorm party
or frat party.

06:01.629 --> 06:04.398
"Which is gonna
rage harder?"

06:04.432 --> 06:08.602
Yeah. And which is gonna
be easier for JJ's wheelchair?

06:08.636 --> 06:11.271
**

06:11.304 --> 06:14.908
"You don't need
to worry about that. Cool?"

06:14.942 --> 06:17.711
Yeah, yeah, we're cool.
We're cool.

06:17.745 --> 06:20.113
Now, I don't see any reason
for you to be cold...

06:20.147 --> 06:22.215
[ Chuckles ]

06:22.249 --> 06:25.453
"Ray, I left Mom home
for a reason."

06:25.486 --> 06:27.354
Oh. No looking out
for you.

06:27.387 --> 06:28.456
I get it.

06:28.489 --> 06:30.223
You don't believe me?
[ Scoffs ]

06:30.257 --> 06:31.425
Well, go explore, then.

06:31.459 --> 06:33.761
Yeah, I'll hook up
with you two later.

06:34.995 --> 06:36.897
Go on! Shoo!

06:36.930 --> 06:38.432
Don't follow him.

06:38.466 --> 06:39.633
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:39.667 --> 06:40.934
Oh.

06:40.968 --> 06:43.971
Maybe a little "Rejection Bingo"
can kill some time.

06:44.004 --> 06:45.473
**

06:45.506 --> 06:46.807
[ Young women laughing ]

06:46.840 --> 06:48.542
Okay. Bingo.
What's next?

06:48.576 --> 06:50.611
**

06:50.644 --> 06:52.780
All right.
Coast is clear.

06:52.813 --> 06:55.315
Except for her.

06:55.348 --> 06:57.117
I'm not hiding
from this one.

06:58.786 --> 07:01.154
Jimmy!
Their faces are on this.

07:02.923 --> 07:05.158
Nina Thompson.

07:05.192 --> 07:06.627
Maya DiMeo.

07:06.660 --> 07:08.428
You still doing
your stupid know-it-all

07:08.462 --> 07:09.663
special-needs blog,
are you?

07:09.697 --> 07:11.932
No. My blogging days
are over.

07:11.965 --> 07:14.234
I'm with
SoCal Abilities Journal.

07:14.267 --> 07:15.503
[ Chuckling ] Well...

07:15.536 --> 07:19.673
that is very bad news
for me.

07:19.707 --> 07:21.141
[ Upbeat music plays ]

07:21.174 --> 07:23.076
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:23.110 --> 07:26.847
**

07:26.880 --> 07:28.115
What's going on, bro?

07:28.148 --> 07:31.351
"I feel like
I'm being followed."

07:31.384 --> 07:38.391
**

07:39.159 --> 07:46.166
**

07:46.333 --> 07:47.935
Okay. Yes, yes!

07:47.968 --> 07:49.803
I am here
to look after you,

07:49.837 --> 07:51.138
and I'm stalking you.

07:51.171 --> 07:54.107
I don't see why
we can't just party together

07:54.141 --> 07:55.643
and I can have your back.

07:56.744 --> 07:58.846
I don't know how
I'm so good at this.

07:58.879 --> 08:00.013
I've never done it before.

08:00.047 --> 08:01.815
But I'm not going away.

08:01.849 --> 08:03.817
I'm sorry, J-- Whoa!

08:08.756 --> 08:09.489
So, what's your beef
with this woman?

08:10.658 --> 08:12.492
Well, so, you know
how I'm a trailblazer?

08:12.526 --> 08:17.130
Nina and I actually shared the
very first Internet "flame war."

08:17.164 --> 08:20.300
And it was at a time
before people really realized

08:20.333 --> 08:23.203
that what one said online
was both public and permanent.

08:23.236 --> 08:24.538
You know, 2004.

08:26.106 --> 08:29.076
I was just an impressionable
new special-needs mom,

08:29.109 --> 08:31.712
and Nina had this parenting blog
with all the answers.

08:31.745 --> 08:34.414
I mean, if Nina said,
"JJ needs to sleep upside down,"

08:34.447 --> 08:36.584
or, "JJ needs to interact more
with horses,"

08:36.617 --> 08:38.686
Jimmy and I were both
huge believers.

08:39.687 --> 08:41.589
In time, I realized

08:41.622 --> 08:44.925
she did not know
what she was talking about.

08:44.958 --> 08:46.426
So then I posted
a takedown.

08:46.459 --> 08:48.395
She posted a takedown
of my takedown,

08:48.428 --> 08:50.097
and it didn't actually end

08:50.130 --> 08:52.332
until the President
of the Internet himself

08:52.365 --> 08:54.768
emailed me,
demanding that I stop.

08:54.802 --> 08:57.037
Pretty wild, eh?

08:58.038 --> 08:59.406
Melanie:
Okay. We're partners --

08:59.439 --> 09:02.442
with a contract that
I insisted we sign -- wow.

09:02.475 --> 09:03.777
Look,
we did not come this far

09:03.811 --> 09:05.713
to let a 15-year-old grudge
sink this company.

09:05.746 --> 09:07.581
Can you apologize?

09:07.615 --> 09:08.415
I don't know.

09:08.448 --> 09:09.617
[ Snaps fingers ]
Follow.

09:09.650 --> 09:11.619
**

09:11.652 --> 09:15.388
Internetprez1@hotmail.com.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.725
See, I'm giving you
your space.

09:17.758 --> 09:19.893
I'm not like Mom.

09:19.927 --> 09:23.130
Although, that lei
is a bit of a choking hazard.

09:23.163 --> 09:24.598
**

09:24.632 --> 09:26.600
"You here to make sure
I'm safe?

09:26.634 --> 09:29.870
I'll be unsafe
until you leave."

09:29.903 --> 09:31.438
What does that even mean?

09:31.471 --> 09:35.142
**

09:35.175 --> 09:36.443
You wouldn't.

09:36.476 --> 09:38.311
[ Clicks, motor whirring ]

09:39.312 --> 09:40.781
[ Indistinct shouting ]

09:40.814 --> 09:42.449
-Come on, man!
-Come on, man!

09:42.482 --> 09:43.651
[ Indistinct shouting ]

09:43.684 --> 09:45.252
Young man: Come on, man!

09:45.285 --> 09:47.254
[ Sighs ] It is really
taking them a while.

09:47.287 --> 09:48.255
Excuse me.

09:48.288 --> 09:49.456
Yes. Can I help you?

09:49.489 --> 09:50.658
These are remarkable.

09:50.691 --> 09:51.892
Do they use magnets?

09:51.925 --> 09:53.226
Uh, sure do.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.629
Same technology they use
on the...space shuttle.

09:55.663 --> 09:56.764
[ Lowered voice ]
There's got to be a magnet

09:56.797 --> 09:57.898
on the space shuttle,
right?

09:57.931 --> 09:58.966
These are fantastic.

09:58.999 --> 10:01.068
You know, it's so refreshing
to see someone

10:01.101 --> 10:04.004
doing something
that really matters.

10:04.037 --> 10:05.305
Matters?

10:05.338 --> 10:06.807
[ Lowered voice ]
You hear that? We matters.

10:06.840 --> 10:07.941
[ Chuckles ]

10:07.975 --> 10:10.010
Come and get your
space-shuttle pants!

10:10.043 --> 10:12.946
Huckster.
Whore. Sellout...

10:12.980 --> 10:14.748
I said
some terrible things,

10:14.782 --> 10:16.516
but, I mean,
it was all in the past.

10:16.549 --> 10:17.584
Water under the bridge.

10:17.617 --> 10:18.618
Bridge troll...

10:18.652 --> 10:20.620
Look, what I said
was inexcusable.

10:20.654 --> 10:22.122
I'm sorry.

10:22.155 --> 10:23.657
Please accept my apology.

10:23.691 --> 10:25.693
I'd wanted that
for years.

10:25.726 --> 10:27.127
No. Never.

10:27.160 --> 10:29.797
Wait.
Are you vendors here?

10:29.830 --> 10:31.865
Oh. You don't know
what we're selling.

10:31.899 --> 10:34.601
No, but I'd love
to give you a write-up.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.770
Accessible hot dogs!
They don't make any sense!

10:36.804 --> 10:37.971
Have a field day!

10:38.005 --> 10:40.974
[ Laughter ]

10:41.008 --> 10:43.343
Oh, no.

10:43.376 --> 10:44.611
JJ!

10:44.644 --> 10:46.646
**

10:46.680 --> 10:48.448
[ Laughs ]

10:48.481 --> 10:49.482
[ Grunts ]

10:49.516 --> 10:52.986
[ Cheers and applause ]

10:53.020 --> 10:54.154
Listen to me.

10:54.187 --> 10:55.856
This is the breakthrough
we have been looking for.

10:55.889 --> 10:58.058
You think of academics
as Ray's domain,

10:58.091 --> 11:00.027
but we can
make it yours, too.

11:00.060 --> 11:00.961
How?

11:00.994 --> 11:02.896
I am going to hypnotize you

11:02.930 --> 11:06.133
so that you can confront Ray
in a safe setting.

11:06.166 --> 11:08.168
Please. That's not
gonna work on me.

11:08.201 --> 11:10.470
Mr. Powers' voice: Would you
please just give it a chance?

11:10.503 --> 11:12.005
Whoa! Ray?

11:12.039 --> 11:13.640
Hypnosis is awesome!

11:13.673 --> 11:14.708
That's impossible.

11:14.742 --> 11:16.643
I haven't even
done anything yet.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.879
Fine,
let's just go with it.

11:18.912 --> 11:22.149
Confront me -- Ray.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.316
Can do.

11:23.350 --> 11:25.318
No, talk to me
and tell me

11:25.352 --> 11:28.421
how I am an obstacle
for your personal growth.

11:28.455 --> 11:31.491
And I would do that to Ray
by pounding him.

11:31.524 --> 11:32.492
Ohh! Uh!

11:32.525 --> 11:34.227
Just let me whale on you!

11:34.261 --> 11:36.997
I am not letting someone
beat me up for a breakthrough.
[ Breathing sharply ]

11:37.030 --> 11:38.165
I have done that once,

11:38.198 --> 11:40.700
and the class never
looked at me the same.

11:40.734 --> 11:41.735
[ Grunting ]

11:41.769 --> 11:42.770
And wake up!

11:42.803 --> 11:43.971
**

11:45.605 --> 11:46.606
Ugh!

11:46.639 --> 11:48.175
Let's just face it.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.143
Ray is the smart one.

11:50.811 --> 11:52.813
Are those nachos
still not ready?

11:53.947 --> 11:56.683
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.
Hey! Hey! You get a shirt!

11:56.716 --> 11:58.451
And you get a T-shirt!

11:58.485 --> 11:59.452
Those are the prototypes!

11:59.486 --> 12:00.888
Okay, I'm gonna
need those back!

12:00.921 --> 12:03.290
Excuse me. Did I --
Did I put this on him right?

12:03.323 --> 12:05.625
I-I -- You're asking me.
Well, that feels good.

12:05.658 --> 12:06.693
I don't know.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.962
Wow. How amazing
is this company?

12:08.996 --> 12:11.431
I'm from the expo,
and we'd love to talk to you.

12:11.464 --> 12:12.800
I don't see why not.

12:12.833 --> 12:13.967
Hey, would you like
a keychain?

12:14.001 --> 12:16.103
-Oh. I would love one.
-Yes, I'd like one.

12:16.136 --> 12:17.938
We don't have any.
But, right?

12:17.971 --> 12:20.107
Okay, "JJ Knoxville."

12:20.140 --> 12:21.975
"Are you done being Mom?"

12:22.009 --> 12:23.276
**

12:23.310 --> 12:26.079
"I just wanted
to let loose together."

12:26.113 --> 12:29.649
I could do that
and still have your back.

12:29.682 --> 12:32.619
Man, JJ, you have no idea
what it is like

12:32.652 --> 12:36.123
to try and help someone
who fights you at every turn.

12:36.156 --> 12:39.993
"You have no idea
what it is to have fun."

12:40.027 --> 12:41.661
Right. I'm the problem.

12:41.694 --> 12:43.130
Boring Ray!

12:43.163 --> 12:45.498
Well, would Boring Ray
chug a beer?

12:45.532 --> 12:46.834
**

12:46.867 --> 12:48.468
Mnh-mnh!

12:48.501 --> 12:51.438
Oh, and now
for too much dessert.

12:51.471 --> 12:54.441
[ Crowd cheering ]

12:54.474 --> 12:55.909
Whoa! Wild man!

12:55.943 --> 12:58.678
Finally, someone who sees
how cool I am.

12:58.711 --> 12:59.947
[ Groans ]

12:59.980 --> 13:02.182
That one sip of that beer
is not sitting well with me.

13:02.215 --> 13:04.284
You just ate
five shots of vodka.

13:04.317 --> 13:06.186
Whoo!
[ Crowd cheering ]

13:06.219 --> 13:08.321
Okay, so, somebody
write this down --

13:08.355 --> 13:11.191
my blood type
is B-negative!

13:11.224 --> 13:12.525
Hi, everyone.

13:12.559 --> 13:14.461
For our
Toast of the Conference Q&A...
Boys?

13:14.494 --> 13:15.795
Where'd they go?
We have to get out of here.

13:15.829 --> 13:17.764
...we'd like to welcome
a few hand-picked businesses

13:17.797 --> 13:19.799
that really stood out
today.

13:19.833 --> 13:21.801
[ Applause ]

13:21.835 --> 13:23.003
What the...

13:23.036 --> 13:24.604
Either they've been invited
on the panel,

13:24.637 --> 13:26.473
or they think
that's the bathroom.

13:26.506 --> 13:28.041
Both:
Bathroom-bathroom-bathroom-
bathroom-bathroom-bathroom...

13:28.075 --> 13:29.476
[ Both groan ]

13:29.509 --> 13:30.677
Nina:
Jimmy and Kenneth,

13:30.710 --> 13:33.546
you've made
quite an impression here today.

13:33.580 --> 13:35.182
Jimmy:
Uh, thank you, Nina.

13:35.215 --> 13:39.052
The response has been truly --
wow, what's the word?

13:39.086 --> 13:39.953
"Omnipotous."

13:39.987 --> 13:41.354
Nope.

13:41.388 --> 13:44.657
Providing adaptive clothing
for folks with disabilities

13:44.691 --> 13:48.228
has been our sole purpose
in life.

13:48.261 --> 13:51.131
[ Audience awws ]
I-Is it clothing
you design yourselves?

13:51.164 --> 13:54.167
Or do you adapt
existing clothes?

13:54.201 --> 13:55.702
Great question.

13:55.735 --> 13:57.304
I'm not sure.

13:57.337 --> 13:59.039
Super smart question.
Thank you for that.

13:59.072 --> 14:01.474
I've got a sample
right here.

14:01.508 --> 14:03.576
How much would
these jeans cost?

14:05.845 --> 14:07.547
[ Both murmuring ]

14:07.580 --> 14:08.848
I want to --
I want to say 12 bucks?

14:08.882 --> 14:10.350
-What?!
-Oh, come on.

14:10.383 --> 14:11.851
Do -- [ Sighs ]

14:11.885 --> 14:13.753
Actually, I swung by
your booth earlier.

14:13.786 --> 14:15.855
I-I seem to remember it costing
a little more than that.

14:15.889 --> 14:17.824
Something around $70?

14:17.857 --> 14:19.927
$70 -- yeah, Kenneth
is more of the numbers guy.

14:19.960 --> 14:23.730
That I am -- one-two...
three-four-five.
See?

14:23.763 --> 14:25.098
Nina: Wow. $70?

14:25.132 --> 14:28.701
The name Fashion 4 All:
Accessible Clothing

14:28.735 --> 14:30.437
would suggest
a more accessible price.

14:30.470 --> 14:31.604
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

14:31.638 --> 14:33.340
I-I-I-I'd like
to speak to that, if I may.

14:33.373 --> 14:34.441
Don't give her the mic.

14:34.474 --> 14:35.842
[ Projecting ]
Oh, not a problem, I'll yell.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.111
The point is to modify
designer clothing

14:38.145 --> 14:40.213
so that people
with disabilities can wear it.

14:40.247 --> 14:42.849
Traditionally, their options
have been super limited.

14:42.882 --> 14:44.851
So the fact that
it's a premium clothing line

14:44.884 --> 14:46.586
is precisely the point.

14:46.619 --> 14:49.923
Is the...impression I got
when I went by the booth.

14:49.957 --> 14:53.093
People are here to learn
about this wonderful company.

14:53.126 --> 14:55.362
They want to hear
from the founders, not you.

14:55.395 --> 14:57.064
Oh, you want to hear
from the founders?

14:57.097 --> 14:58.265
Oh, you will, but first,
say some more

14:58.298 --> 14:59.866
about how great
this company is.

14:59.899 --> 15:03.203
Yeah, and then get ready for the
biggest surprise of your life.

15:03.236 --> 15:04.771
You're the founders,
aren't you?

15:09.609 --> 15:10.443
Yes, we are the people
behind the company,

15:11.678 --> 15:14.214
and, yes, we've had run-ins
with many of you.

15:14.247 --> 15:15.782
But you all seem
to like our product.

15:15.815 --> 15:17.284
So can we answer
any questions?

15:17.317 --> 15:18.485
[ Crowd murmuring ]

15:18.518 --> 15:20.988
To be clear --
questions about the company,

15:21.021 --> 15:24.557
not questions about things
we did to make you hate us.

15:24.591 --> 15:25.625
[ Crowd murmuring ]

15:25.658 --> 15:26.459
Ah.

15:26.493 --> 15:27.727
[ Whispering
indistinctly ]

15:27.760 --> 15:30.663
No, I don't think we're
gonna get the panelist swag bag.

15:31.531 --> 15:33.967
[ Cellphone ringing ]

15:34.001 --> 15:35.468
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Yo.

15:35.502 --> 15:37.404
Hey, tell that JJ kid
his brother had a few too many.

15:37.437 --> 15:38.471
[ Crowd cheering ]

15:38.505 --> 15:40.273
[ Slurring ] Everyone!

15:40.307 --> 15:45.245
Who wants to see
a Mathemagician?

15:45.278 --> 15:47.480
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

15:47.514 --> 15:48.581
Where you guys going?

15:48.615 --> 15:49.649
Well, we're done.

15:49.682 --> 15:51.684
That's our audience,
and they hate us.

15:51.718 --> 15:53.120
So you're just gonna quit?

15:53.153 --> 15:55.122
No. I-I'm not gonna
let this happen.

15:55.155 --> 15:57.657
I don't know
a lot of ways to matter,

15:57.690 --> 16:00.793
but I know how to pick you up
when you're down.

16:00.827 --> 16:02.195
Me too?

16:02.229 --> 16:05.865
Well, it's really
kind of a Maya-specific deal,

16:05.898 --> 16:07.000
no, but, okay.

16:07.034 --> 16:08.168
Uh...

16:08.201 --> 16:11.471
You are
Maya freaking DiMeo --

16:11.504 --> 16:13.640
and you are Melanie.

16:13.673 --> 16:17.510
You are the strongest,
sexiest woman I have ever met.

16:17.544 --> 16:20.513
[ Clicks tongue ]
That is a nice haircut.

16:20.547 --> 16:22.549
You are a fighter.

16:22.582 --> 16:24.051
I am a fighter.

16:24.084 --> 16:25.952
That's how you got here
in the first place.

16:25.985 --> 16:27.987
Now go up there and fight.

16:28.021 --> 16:29.956
And win.

16:29.989 --> 16:32.025
Now, normally,
at this point in the talk,

16:32.059 --> 16:35.395
there would be some sort
of energizing butt slap,

16:35.428 --> 16:36.796
given the whole...

16:36.829 --> 16:39.199
**

16:39.232 --> 16:42.069
You meant you slapping
their butts, didn't you?

16:42.102 --> 16:45.205
You've got to ask for what you
want in this world, all right?

16:45.238 --> 16:46.473
Ahh.

16:46.506 --> 16:47.874
Let's face it.

16:47.907 --> 16:50.643
There's just room
for one smart kid in my family.

16:50.677 --> 16:51.978
Call your brother.

16:52.011 --> 16:53.146
Your real brother.

16:53.180 --> 16:56.183
Not the one you've
built up in your head.

16:56.216 --> 16:57.750
Tell him what you told me.

16:57.784 --> 17:00.920
**

17:00.953 --> 17:02.089
[ Sighs ]

17:02.122 --> 17:03.090
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:03.123 --> 17:04.224
[ Rings ]

17:04.257 --> 17:06.259
[ Chuckling ]
Dylaaaaaaaaan!

17:06.293 --> 17:07.860
Wait, a-are you drunk?

17:07.894 --> 17:10.697
[ Slurring ] Could a drunk
do a backflip like this?

17:10.730 --> 17:11.698
Ohh!
[ Thuds ]

17:11.731 --> 17:12.765
-Dude!
-Ohh.

17:12.799 --> 17:14.601
Yeah, I'm drunk.
What's up?

17:14.634 --> 17:16.703
Apparently,
I could be smart,

17:16.736 --> 17:19.172
but I'm not
because that's your thing.

17:19.206 --> 17:20.940
Of course you're smart.

17:20.973 --> 17:23.543
You are the smartest
person I know.

17:23.576 --> 17:26.913
The schemes and pranks
you come up with?

17:26.946 --> 17:30.217
We are basically
your puppets.

17:30.250 --> 17:33.019
Hey! I'm gonna
do puppets next!

17:33.052 --> 17:35.422
Wow, Ray. Thanks.

17:35.455 --> 17:36.623
[ Voice breaking ]
And, Dylan?

17:36.656 --> 17:38.925
If I can get really...

17:38.958 --> 17:40.593
really real with you
right --

17:40.627 --> 17:43.096
[ Cellphone beeps ]
You know, I think
my problem's solved.

17:43.130 --> 17:44.431
Because Ray believes in you

17:44.464 --> 17:47.100
and the only obstacle is the one
you put up for yourself?

17:47.134 --> 17:49.702
No, because he was being
drunk and dumb.

17:49.736 --> 17:51.538
If Ray can be dumb
every once in a while,

17:51.571 --> 17:52.939
then maybe I can be smart.

17:52.972 --> 17:56.376
Great. Now let's talk strategies
for getting those grades up.

17:56.409 --> 17:57.944
Grades?
I'm smart.

17:57.977 --> 18:00.747
I eschew that sort
of external validation.

18:00.780 --> 18:03.816
Cool! Now I can blow people off
with Ray words.

18:03.850 --> 18:05.785
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:05.818 --> 18:08.455
[ Slurring ] JJ!
I missed you, man.

18:08.488 --> 18:11.258
"Time to go, Ray.
Put down the hose."

18:11.291 --> 18:15.295
No. No. This is my [bleep] hose!
I brought the hose.

18:15.328 --> 18:16.596
Give it back.

18:16.629 --> 18:18.331
Go get the --
Go get the hose.

18:18.365 --> 18:19.832
And turn on the siren.

18:19.866 --> 18:20.867
Whoop, whoop!

18:22.969 --> 18:25.138
You suck
at driving this thing.

18:25.172 --> 18:26.506
-[ Sighs ]
-Geez.

18:26.539 --> 18:28.175
There's nothing worse
than a guy who needs your help

18:28.208 --> 18:29.509
but won't take it.

18:29.542 --> 18:31.077
[ Yawns ]

18:31.110 --> 18:34.013
**

18:34.046 --> 18:35.248
[ Snores ]

18:35.282 --> 18:38.117
[ Wheelchair beeps ]

18:38.151 --> 18:39.619
[ Thud ]

18:39.652 --> 18:41.120
Where are we?

18:41.154 --> 18:44.424
And now, welcome
to the stage a man who --

18:44.457 --> 18:46.593
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Sit down, shorty.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.928
Right. We're back.
We've got a few things to say.

18:48.961 --> 18:50.597
First things first --
thanks, Jimmy,

18:50.630 --> 18:52.199
for forgetting
to give back your microphone.

18:52.232 --> 18:53.933
You're welcome.

18:53.966 --> 18:55.502
Kenneth forgot his, too.

18:55.535 --> 18:57.136
Now, have we wronged you?

18:57.170 --> 18:58.471
Yes.

18:58.505 --> 18:59.939
Are we sorry?

18:59.972 --> 19:01.341
Case by case.

19:01.374 --> 19:04.611
But the fight we put into making
life better for our boys

19:04.644 --> 19:06.613
we also put
into these clothes.

19:06.646 --> 19:08.881
Look, you guys know
what this life is.

19:08.915 --> 19:10.550
I mean, we'll do anything
for our kids.

19:10.583 --> 19:12.285
And these clothes
will make your kids happy.

19:12.319 --> 19:13.653
I mean, I promise you,

19:13.686 --> 19:15.722
they will love these pants
even more than y'all hate us.

19:15.755 --> 19:16.956
[ Crowd murmuring ]

19:16.989 --> 19:19.626
Show of hands.
Who wants to hear a bit more?

19:19.659 --> 19:21.528
[ Audience murmuring ]

19:22.829 --> 19:24.130
Okay, great.

19:24.163 --> 19:27.334
Then let us start fresh
and reintroduce ourselves.

19:27.367 --> 19:28.167
I'm Melanie.

19:28.201 --> 19:29.536
And I'm Maya.

19:29.569 --> 19:31.504
And we're two
special-needs mums...

19:31.538 --> 19:32.805
Both:
...who want to make a difference

19:32.839 --> 19:37.009
in the lives of families
with children with disabilities.

19:37.043 --> 19:38.511
I finally get it.

19:38.545 --> 19:39.546
[ Voice breaking ]
It's beautiful.

19:39.579 --> 19:42.148
[ Clicks, motor whirring ]

19:42.181 --> 19:45.452
Hey!
I'm in Cirque du So-Ray.

19:47.954 --> 19:48.921
[ Clicks, whirring stops ]

19:48.955 --> 19:51.224
You wanted
to let loose.

19:51.258 --> 19:53.393
We did it.

19:53.426 --> 19:55.395
We both got wasted,
right?

19:55.428 --> 20:03.670
**

20:03.703 --> 20:06.239
Hey, I'm trying to sleep.

20:06.273 --> 20:08.140
[ Groans ]

20:09.609 --> 20:12.745
"Not 'til you read this --

20:12.779 --> 20:14.714
We're brothers.

20:14.747 --> 20:17.950
We should
look out for each other.

20:17.984 --> 20:22.922
It's not easy for me
to accept your help.

20:22.955 --> 20:25.191
But I love you for it, Ray.

20:25.224 --> 20:27.093
I really do."

20:27.126 --> 20:28.628
That's nice.

20:28.661 --> 20:30.763
But can you tell me
when I'm not drunk

20:30.797 --> 20:32.164
so I can remember it?

20:32.999 --> 20:35.968
Ah, damn, I think
I already forgot it.

20:36.002 --> 20:37.537
**

20:37.570 --> 20:39.372
Oh, and, JJ...

20:39.406 --> 20:40.707
[Voice breaking]
...can I be really,

20:40.740 --> 20:43.042
really real with you
right now?

20:43.075 --> 20:45.111
**

20:45.144 --> 20:46.145
I l--

20:46.178 --> 20:47.947
[ Vomiting ]

20:47.980 --> 20:50.149
It came out.

20:54.787 --> 20:55.254
Are you sure about this?

20:56.122 --> 20:57.123
I'm smart now.

20:57.156 --> 20:58.224
At max velocity,

20:58.257 --> 21:00.493
your momentum
will be arrested by impact

21:00.527 --> 21:02.662
with these Amorpha fruticosa.

21:02.695 --> 21:04.997
Say your phrase
and jump off the roof.

21:05.031 --> 21:06.399
Uh...Hi.

21:06.433 --> 21:07.834
I'm Ray DiMeo,

21:07.867 --> 21:11.504
and this
is Tiny Parachute Jump.

21:12.839 --> 21:14.073
[ Screams ]
[ Thumps ]

21:14.106 --> 21:15.742
[ Laughs ]
You jumped into a bush

21:15.775 --> 21:17.610
because I learned
two Latin words?

21:17.644 --> 21:19.479
Being smart rules!

21:19.512 --> 21:21.180
[ Laughs ]
Say "hi," Ray.

21:21.213 --> 21:24.183
Smart Dylan is gonna
be a problem, isn't it?
Yeah.
